"content": "<style>\nh1.thlex-title { font-size: 1.3em; margin: 0 0 0.4em; }\n.thlex-key { color: #888; font-size: 0.85em; font-weight: normal; margin-right: 0.4em; }\nnav.thlex-index { margin: 0.5em 0 0.75em; }\nnav.thlex-index ul { margin: 0; padding-left: 1.2em; }\nnav.thlex-index li { margin: 0.15em 0; font-size: 0.95em; }\n.thlex-section { margin: 0.6em 0; }\nh2.thlex-heading { font-size: 1em; margin: 0.5em 0 0.2em; }\nh3.thlex-subheading { font-size: 0.95em; font-weight: normal; font-style: italic; margin: 0.2em 0; }\n.thlex-language-sets { margin: 0.3em 0 0.3em 1em; }\n.thlex-language-set { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 0.75em; border-left: 3px solid #e0e0e0; }\n.thlex-language { font-size: 0.8em; color: #888; margin-right: 0.4em; }\n.thlex-lemma { font-weight: bold; font-family: serif; }\n.thlex-translit { color: #555; font-style: italic; font-size: 0.9em; margin-left: 0.3em; }\n.thlex-refs { font-size: 0.85em; color: #444; margin-top: 0.15em; }\n.thlex-paragraphs p { margin: 0.35em 0; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.5; }\n.thlex-image { margin: 0.5em 0; display: block; }\n.thlex-image img { max-width: 100%; height: auto; display: block; }\nfigcaption.thlex-caption { font-size: 0.85em; color: #555; font-style: italic; margin-top: 0.2em; }\n.thlex-abbr { border-bottom: 1px dotted #888; cursor: help; }\n.thlex-xref { color: #1a5fb4; }\nspan[data-bnType=\"bibleReference\"] { color: #1a5fb4; }\ntable.thlex-table { border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 0.9em; margin: 0.5em 0; }\ntable.thlex-table td { padding: 0.2em 0.6em; vertical-align: top; border: 1px solid #ddd; }\ntable.thlex-table tr:first-child td { font-weight: bold; background: #f5f5f5; }\nul.thlex-index-list { margin: 0.4em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; font-size: 0.95em; line-height: 1.6; }\nul.thlex-index-list ul { margin: 0.1em 0; padding-left: 1.4em; }\n.thlex-index-key { font-weight: bold; font-style: italic; }\n</style><h1 class=\"thlex-title\" id=\"REALIA:5.4\"><span class=\"thlex-key\">5.4</span> Torch</h1><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">References:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-sets\">\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Hebrew</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">לַפִּיד</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(lapid)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen15:17\">GEN 15:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg7:16\">JDG 7:16</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg7:20\">JDG 7:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg15:4\">JDG 15:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg15:4\">JDG 15:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg15:5\">JDG 15:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job41:11\">JOB 41:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa62:1\">ISA 62:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek1:13\">EZK 1:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Dan10:6\">DAN 10:6</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Nah2:5\">NAM 2:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Zech12:6\">ZEC 12:6</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">δᾳδουχία</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(dadouchia)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Macc4:22\">2MA 4:22</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-lemma\">λαμπάς</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(lampas)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:1\">MAT 25:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:4\">MAT 25:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:7\">MAT 25:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt25:8\">MAT 25:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:3\">JHN 18:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:8\">ACT 20:8</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:5\">REV 4:5</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev8:10\">REV 8:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jdt10:22\">JDT 10:22</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Sir48:1\">SIR 48:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Macc6:39\">1MA 6:39</a></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"thlex-language-set\">\n<span class=\"thlex-language\">Greek</span> <span class=\"thlex-translit\">(fōs)</span>\n<div class=\"thlex-refs\"><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:29\">ACT 16:29</a></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Description and usage:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>\n            <figure class=\"thlex-image\"><img class=\"thlex-img\" src=\"images/WEB-0475_torch.jpg\" alt=\"Flaming torches\"><figcaption class=\"thlex-caption\">Flaming torches (© Andrew Dunn, CC BY-SA 2.0, via Wikimedia Commons)</figcaption></figure>The torch was a burning stick or bundle of sticks carried about as a light. In order to lengthen the time of burning, one end of the stick could be wrapped with cloth, which was soaked in a flammable substance such as pitch.</p>\n<hr/>\n</div>\n</div><div class=\"thlex-section\">\n<h2 class=\"thlex-heading\">Translation:</h2>\n<div class=\"thlex-paragraphs\">\n<p>In modern British English, a “torch” is a handheld electric light powered by batteries, that is, a “flashlight” in American English. Such a word would be entirely out of place in the translation of the Bible.</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job41:13\">JOB 41:13</a>: Here the focus is on the flame, not on the torch that contains the flame, so for the first line of this verse <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> has “Flames blaze from his mouth.”</p>\n<p>While the Greek word <em>lampas</em> most properly refers to a “torch,” in some places (for example, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts20:8\">ACT 20:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev4:5\">REV 4:5</a>) some translations prefer the English derived term “lamp.”</p>\n<p>Some languages may find it difficult to distinguish between “torches” and “lanterns” in <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John18:3\">JHN 18:3</a>. It is possible to say “burning sticks and containers with small fires for light.” See also the discussion <a class=\"thlex-xref\" data-bnType=\"lexiconLink\" data-collection=\"\" data-key=\"\" href=\"#\">5.3 Lantern&lt;REALIA:5.3&gt;</a>.</p>\n<p>\n            <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:29\">ACT 16:29</a>: The jailer demanded that “lights” be brought, but the text does not indicate the specific instruments. Many languages will be able to follow the pattern of <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"Good News Translation (1992)\">GNT</abbr> and <abbr class=\"thlex-abbr\" title=\"German Common Language Version (Gute Nachricht Bibel)\">GECL</abbr> by beginning this verse with “The jailer called for a light.” It is likely that torches from the entrance to the jail would have been most readily available. However, the intention of the jailer will be adequately expressed also with “The jailer called for someone to bring a lamp.”</p>\n</div>\n</div>",
